This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as entity identification. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel neural architecture for multitasking, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimizing the tasks jointly, which is a common theme in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed architecture involves embeddings, which is a common technique in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves segment-level representation, which is a common theme in computer vision tasks.
